    "numpy_ref": "np.correlate",
    "category": "counted_custom",
    "status": "supported",
    "weight": 1.0,
    "cost_formula": "n * m",
    "cost_formula_latex": "$n \\cdot m$",
    "notes": "1-D cross-correlation.",
    "summary": "Cross-correlation of two 1-dimensional sequences.",
    "signature": "we.correlate(a, v, mode='valid')"
  },
  "docs": {
    "sections": [
      {
        "kind": "summary",
        "title": "Summary",
        "blocks": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "Cross-correlation of two 1-dimensional sequences."
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "This function computes the correlation as generally defined in signal\nprocessing texts [1]_:"
          },
          {
            "type": "directive",
            "name": "math:: c_k = \\sum_n a_{n+k} \\cdot \\overline{v}_n",
            "body": "",
            "raw": ".. math:: c_k = \\sum_n a_{n+k} \\cdot \\overline{v}_n"
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "with a and v sequences being zero-padded where necessary and\n:math:`\\overline v` denoting complex conjugation."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "kind": "parameters",
        "title": "Parameters",
        "items": [
          {
            "name": "a, v",
            "type": "array_like",
            "desc_blocks": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "Input sequences."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "name": "mode",
            "type": "{'valid', 'same', 'full'}, optional",
            "desc_blocks": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "Refer to the `convolve` docstring.  Note that the default\nis 'valid', unlike `convolve`, which uses 'full'."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "kind": "returns",
        "title": "Returns",
        "items": [
          {
            "name": "out",
            "type": "ndarray",
            "desc_blocks": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "Discrete cross-correlation of `a` and `v`."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "kind": "notes",
        "title": "Notes",
        "blocks": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "The definition of correlation above is not unique and sometimes\ncorrelation may be defined differently. Another common definition is [1]_:"
          },
          {
            "type": "directive",
            "name": "math:: c'_k = \\sum_n a_{n} \\cdot \\overline{v_{n+k}}",
            "body": "",
            "raw": ".. math:: c'_k = \\sum_n a_{n} \\cdot \\overline{v_{n+k}}"
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "which is related to :math:`c_k` by :math:`c'_k = c_{-k}`."
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "`numpy.correlate` may perform slowly in large arrays (i.e. n = 1e5)\nbecause it does not use the FFT to compute the convolution; in that case,\n`scipy.signal.correlate` might be preferable."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "kind": "examples",
        "title": "Examples",
        "blocks": [
          {
            "type": "code",
            "language": "text",
            "code": ">>> import numpy as np\n>>> np.correlate([1, 2, 3], [0, 1, 0.5])\narray([3.5])\n>>> np.correlate([1, 2, 3], [0, 1, 0.5], \"same\")\narray([2. ,  3.5,  3. ])\n>>> np.correlate([1, 2, 3], [0, 1, 0.5], \"full\")\narray([0.5,  2. ,  3.5,  3. ,  0. ])"
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "Using complex sequences:"
          },
          {
            "type": "code",
            "language": "text",
            "code": ">>> np.correlate([1+1j, 2, 3-1j], [0, 1, 0.5j], 'full')\narray([ 0.5-0.5j,  1.0+0.j ,  1.5-1.5j,  3.0-1.j ,  0.0+0.j ])"
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "Note that you get the time reversed, complex conjugated result\n(:math:`\\overline{c_{-k}}`) when the two input sequences a and v change\nplaces:"
          },
          {
            "type": "code",
            "language": "text",
            "code": ">>> np.correlate([0, 1, 0.5j], [1+1j, 2, 3-1j], 'full')\narray([ 0.0+0.j ,  3.0+1.j ,  1.5+1.5j,  1.0+0.j ,  0.5+0.5j])"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "kind": "see-also",
        "title": "See Also",
        "blocks": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "convolve \u2014 Discrete, linear convolution of two one-dimensional sequences."
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "scipy.signal.correlate \u2014 uses FFT which has superior performance on large arrays."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}